we know,
=>â \(z = w_1x_1+ w_2x_2+ ... + w_nx_n+ b\)

in matrix form,

\(\text{W = } \begin{bmatrix} w_1 \\ w_2 \\ . \\ . \\ . \\ w_n \end{bmatrix} , \quad \text{X = } \begin{bmatrix} x_1\\ x_2\\ . \\ . \\ . \\ x_n \end{bmatrix} , \quad \text{b = } \begin{bmatrix} b\\ \end{bmatrix}\)

=>â \(z = \text{W}^T\text{X}+ \text{b}\)

where, \(\text{W}\) is weight matrix, \(\text{X}\) is input matrix and \(\text{b}\) is bias matrix.
